         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">22/3/93 ¶  ¶ From a telegram sent at the day of his funeral published in the Sydney-Morning-Herald, ¶  dear Miss Walker, you may have noticed, how deeply I feel the loss of "my dearest science-friend ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">93.03.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Annie Walker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Am 27/1, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">22/3/93</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>From a telegram sent at the day of his funeral published in the Sydney-Morning-Herald,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Maiden, 15 March 1893, lamenting the death of W. Woolls. Maiden read out M's telegram at Woolls's funeral.</p>
               </note> dear Miss Walker, you may have noticed, how deeply I feel the loss of "my dearest science-friend in Australia". This morning I received from Miss Georgina King a <name key="Cassinia">Cassinia</name>, which our lamented friend had named only 3 or 4 days before his burial. Kindly let me know, whether I shall have the honor of your and the Misses Cole's visit on Friday-morning or in the afternoon,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Annie Walker was evidently visiting Melbourne, presumably with the Ward-Coles at ‘St Ninians’, Brighton.</p>
               </note> so that I may [...]<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">illegible word</seg>.</p>
               </note> as my office-work at that day in such a manner to be free for attending on you, the inspection of your pictures requiring carefulness.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With regardful remembrance of you and best greeting to Mrs Cole and her kind daughters<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Mrs Thomas Anne Cole, and Margaret Morrison and Agnes Bruce Cole [Family often referred to as 'Ward-Cole' in the social pages of newspapers.]</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cassinia">Cassinia</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
